plan_analysis:
The snapshot supplied shows Google very close to #1 today (Feb 26 2026) but still behind Anthropic. Forecasters now need:  
• Base-rate evidence – how often (and for how long) Google/Gemini or any provider has actually held #1 on LM Arena since the leaderboard was launched; frequency and timing of lead changes.  
• Resolution-mechanism details – exactly how Arena score is calculated, how often it updates, and how model names/providers are displayed (so forecasters know what qualifies as “Gemini” and how quickly a new model can appear).  
• Key drivers – whether Google will ship an upgraded Gemini model (e.g., “Ultra 2”) or big tuning push before 15 Mar; likewise whether Anthropic/OpenAI/xAI will counter with their own upgrades.  
• Current state – the very latest leaderboard snapshot (has Google already edged ahead?); any fresh news/rumours of imminent Gemini releases; any reports of Anthropic improvements.  
• Contrarian check – reasons Google might *not* overtake (e.g., evidence of upcoming Anthropic Claude upgrade, voting-pattern quirks, or slower Arena score convergence).

The eight queries below collectively cover those dimensions. Five are historical (base rate, mechanism, release timelines) and three are current (brand-new launches, present leaderboard standings, competitor moves). Exactly one Agent query is used for the quantitative base-rate analysis.

queries_planned.intent: Locate archived snapshots to reconstruct historical #1 rankings and provider turnover.
Find prior occasions where Gemini models topped or nearly topped the leaderboard to gauge precedent.

queries_planned.query: Analyze historical LM Arena #1 provider frequency 2023-2026; calculate days Google held top spot vs Anthropic, OpenAI; include tie periods.
queries_planned.intent: Produce quantitative base-rate statistics of Google/Gemini at #1.
Understand calculation, update cadence, and naming conventions that determine official #1.
Identify publicly known or leaked schedules for new Gemini versions before 15 Mar 2026.
Catch breaking news of any just-released Gemini variant that could boost ranking.
Retrieve the most recent leaderboard snapshot to assess current gap and momentum.
Surface reports of forthcoming Anthropic improvements that could keep them #1, providing a contrarian perspective.
